title: Syllepte vagans
text:
Syllepte vagans, the leaden pearl, is a <a href="moth">moth</a> in the family <a href="Crambidae">Crambidae</a>. It was described by Tutt in 1890. It is found in <a href="South%20Africa">South Africa</a>, <a href="Botswana">Botswana</a>, the <a href="Democratic%20Republic%20of%20Congo">Democratic Republic of Congo</a>, <a href="Kenya">Kenya</a>, <a href="Mozambique">Mozambique</a>, <a href="Namibia">Namibia</a>, <a href="Nigeria">Nigeria</a>, <a href="Tanzania">Tanzania</a>, <a href="Zambia">Zambia</a> and <a href="Zimbabwe">Zimbabwe</a>. It is recorded infrequently in the <a href="Great%20Britain">Great Britain</a> through accidental import.
